<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./442: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cook</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-25T15:00:00-04:00">May 25, 1929—3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>18. If you perceive no objection please ask the Venezuelan Government
                                to continue the temporary operating permit of Pan American <pb facs="0695" n="559" xml:id="pg_559"/> Airways, Incorporated,
                                pending the conclusion of the formal contract and to have the
                                Venezuelan Post Office accept at Maracay mail despatched by the
                                United States Post Office, as requested in the latter’s cablegram of
                                May 4 to the Venezuelan Postal Administration.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>